hentic) according to Al-Bayhaqi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0635\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0639\u064f\u0648\u062f\u064d \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0643\u064f\u0645\u0652 \u0628\u0650\u0627\u0644\u0634\u0651\u0650\u0641\u064e\u0627\u0626\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0642\u064f\u0631\u0652\u0622\u0646\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5460,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/21\/honey-treatment-upset-stomach\/","url_meta":{"origin":32785,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Honey: The Prophet uses honey to treat upset stomach","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 21, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa'id al-Khudri reported: A man came to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \"My brother has diarrhea.\" The Prophet said, \"Give him honey to drink.\" The man gave him honey to drink and he said, \"I gave it to him but his diarrhea only\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26810,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/09\/27\/medicine-hot-sweet-drinks\/","url_meta":{"origin":32785,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Medicine: Hot, sweet, healthy drinks bring comfort","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 27, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"Verily, talbina rests the heart of a sick person and takes away some grief.\" Source:\u00a0S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5365 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari Ibn Hajar said, \"Al-Asma'i said talbina is a broth made from flour or bran,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":18999,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/05\/06\/hijamah-cupping-honey\/","url_meta":{"origin":32785,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hijamah: There is healing in cupping, honey","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 6, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThere is healing in three: a cupping operation, a drink of honey, and cauterization with fire, but I forbid my nation from using cauterization.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5357 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":22323,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/03\/26\/asbab-nuzul-surah-at-tahreem\/","url_meta":{"origin":32785,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Tafsir: Cause of revelation for Surat al-Tahrim","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 26, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would spend time with his wife Zainab bint Jahsh and he would drink a concoction of honey. Hafsa and I agreed that whomever the Prophet visited first, we would say, \u201cI notice a strong odor of mimosa gum on you.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26036,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/03\/12\/prophet-full-stomach-khubz\/","url_meta":{"origin":32785,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Food: The Prophet never filled his stomach with bread","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 12, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, left this world while he had never ate to his fill of barley bread. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5098 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u062e\u064e\u0631\u064e\u062c\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","